<task id="task_CBF553B502414830BA175DD96A697DF2">
  <title>Track Player Events Using AutoTrack</title>
  <shortdesc>AutoTrack automatically tracks video player events such as start,
	 stop, and pause. 
  </shortdesc>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <keyword>media</keyword>
        <keyword>milestone</keyword>
        <keyword>sdk</keyword>
        <keyword>video</keyword>
      </keywords>
      <othermeta name="solution" content="Analytics" />
      <othermeta name="topic" content="Developer and implementation" />
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <taskbody>
    <context id="context_7942D0D81D1F417BB41F6E47E8077496">
      <p>This prevents you from needing to manually track these events and call
		  the open, play, stop, and close methods directly. 
		</p>
      <p>See 
		  <xref href="video_ref_faq.xml#concept_2209A170CE424C94986E01631BF7FC6A/section_734551C1360F4A53B8E4DA7584196E78" type="section" format="dita" scope="local"><?xm-replace_text What is Autotrack??></xref>.
		  
		</p>
    </context>
    <steps id="steps_64A8F0A2AE0644A8A9ACA8C5718408DF">
      <step id="step_0AED1E12F2584BE18CAAF7E089BF4586">
        <cmd>Add the 
			 <codeph>s.Media.autoTrack</codeph> variable and set it to 
			 <codeph>true</codeph>. 
		  </cmd>
        <stepresult>
          <codeblock>s.Media.autoTrack = true;</codeblock>
        </stepresult>
      </step>
    </steps>
    <example id="example_C6FD5A741A9B41ECBE99B82D98CF6429">
      <p>
        <b>Next step:</b>
        <xref href="video_flash_test.xml#task_9B7A519F3E2242B2946229B8D08AB02B" format="dita" scope="local">
          <?xm-replace_text Test Your Video Measurement Code?>
        </xref>.
		  
		</p>
    </example>
  </taskbody>
</task>